The paper proposes a novel approach for learning rules from RDF knowledge bases, which involves mining frequent patterns and generating rules from them. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach also involves working with large-scale knowledge bases, which is a common topic in database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the learned rules, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
